  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Multi-Sector Humanitarian Response for Persons Affected by Violence in Northern Mozambique and the Supporting COVID-19 Vaccination Campaign Roll-Out in Mozambique, Botswana and South Africa</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To address the effects of violence and insecurity in northern Mozambique, IOM&apos;s multi-sectoral response provides humanitarian aid to conflict-affected persons - especially internally displaced persons (IDPs), host communities, and those left behind - while reducing and responding to vulnerabilities and threats. The action includes activities under the protection sector to address humanitarian needs in Cabo Delgado, Niassa, and Nampula provinces. To provide continuous and critical information on displacement numbers and trends as well as needs of conflict-affected persons, IOM is also implementing Displacement Tracking Matrix (DTM) systems to collect and analyze data which will help humanitarian partners target interventions for context-specific assistance and programming. Furthermore, IOM is providing technical and operational support to government and partners in Mozambique, Botswana and South Africa to contribute to access to COVID-19 vaccines in humanitarian settings and migration affected communities.</narrative>
  </description>
